Privacy Policy for Adv.Attachments

Last Updated: April 11, 2026


DATA COLLECTION

Adv.Attachments does not collect, transmit, or store any telemetry, analytics,
or personal data.

All processing occurs locally within your YouTrack instance and your configured
S3 storage.


EXTERNAL SERVICES

The app contacts only:

1. Your configured S3 endpoint — for file storage operations (upload, download,
   list, delete). Only the endpoint you explicitly configure in Admin Settings
   is used.

2. Public CDN (optional) — for preview libraries (docx-preview, SheetJS/xlsx,
   WebODF) only when using the built-in preview engine. To avoid any CDN
   requests, set Preview Engine to "native" in Admin Settings (default).

No other external services are contacted.


DATA PROCESSING

  - The app reads issue attachment metadata via YouTrack's internal API.
  - S3 file operations use presigned URLs generated server-side; credentials
    never leave the backend.
  - Generated presigned URLs are short-lived (configurable TTL) and scoped to
    specific operations.
  - No file content, user data, or credentials are logged or transmitted to
    third parties.
  - S3 credentials are stored in YouTrack App Settings and never returned by
    the API.


CONTACT

For privacy-related questions, contact: apps@mag1.cc
